chapter-3


Loops & Strings
----------------

loops in JS

-Loops are used to execute piece of code again & again 

1. for loop

initialization ; stopping condition ; updation


infinite loop: a loop  that never ends //never ever do this
               stopping condition is not false

2.while loop

while(condition){          initialization
  //                       condition
}



3. d0-while loop

do{
//
}while (condition);


4. for-of loop

for(let val of strVar){
  //
}


5. for-in loop

for(let key in objVar){
  //
}


//Strings in JS
--Strings is a sequence of characters used to represent text


// Template literals in JS
-- A way to have embedded exxpressions in strings
  `this is a template literals`

`string text${expression} string text`;
`this is specialstring ${1+2+3} `;

let output = `the cost ${obj.cost} is ${obj.price} rupees`;

escape characters --doesn't print 
\n -- next line
\t -- tab space


