Chapter-4 

Arrays in JS
-------------

--collection of items (linear)

array in indices

arr[0],arr[1],arr[2],.......


arrays are mutable  //strings are immutable


------------------------------------------------------
Looping over array
--print all elements of an array

array methods

push() : add to end

pop() : delete from end & return 

toString() : converts array to string


unshift()  : add to start -> push
shift()  :delete from start & return ->pop

slice() : returns apiece of the array   ---> slice(startIdx, endIdx)
spice() : change original array (add ,remove, replace)  
                                 ---> splice(startIdx,delCount,newEle)


